Unrealistic MUA Propaganda We’re Smiling Through 😅
Aka: the things that make us scream internally while smiling externally with a brush in hand 🫠💄

🫣 “Can you take a few people off the list last minute?”
We’ve scheduled time, prepped products, and possibly blocked other clients. Changing the count last-minute derails the entire flow—it’s not just a casual swap.

💸 “Can you lower the price? She just wants a little bit of glam.”
Soft glam still takes real skill, premium products, and time. You’re not just paying for pigment—you’re paying for professionalism.

👁️ “Can you make sure my under eyes don’t crease at all?”
Absolutely—right after I invent a way to stop human skin from moving. Creasing is natural, not failure.

🧴 “Primer makes makeup last longer.”
Not always. Primer isn’t a magic glue stick—it’s more about addressing skin texture, oil control, or hydration. Longevity depends on prep, products, and setting techniques, not just primer.

MUA fam, what’s the one myth you wish we could ban forever? 😭 Let’s talk about it below.

✨ Makeup is art, not wizardry. And we’re done romanticizing the propaganda.

✨ You no longer chase what drains you. If something feels unclear or heavy, you honour the feeling and take a step back. Your peace matters more now.

✨ You don’t feel the need to respond instantly anymore. It’s not distance—it’s protecting your energy. You’re learning that urgency doesn’t equal importance.

✨ You walked away from a familiar conversation that once left you anxious—and this time, you didn’t carry the guilt with you. That’s what healing looks like.

✨ You’ve let go of the need to prove your side of the story. No more saving screenshots. You’re choosing calm over chaos, softness over struggle.

✨ You had a tough day and didn’t make it a reflection of your worth. Not every day is good—but that doesn’t mean you’re not.

✨ You noticed an old pattern knocking at your door—and instead of inviting it in, you saw it for what it was and let it pass. That’s growth in action.

✨ You don’t rehearse imaginary conversations anymore. You’ve stopped waiting for someone’s return. You’ve moved forward—for you.

✨ You’re no longer taking the blame for everything that goes wrong. Now, you pause, breathe, and respond with clarity. That’s real self-trust.

✨ You’ve stopped trying to hold it all together on your own. You let people in—even imperfectly. Letting yourself be supported is strength too.

✨ You’re not in a rush to get to what’s next. You’re finding meaning in the in-between. The quiet no longer feels empty—it feels like home.

Whenever you need a gentle nudge, come back to this. You’re doing more healing than you realize. 🤍

Two hearts, one vibe — fresh, radiant, and just the right touch of glam for my cutest couple. 

For this beautiful couple, the goal wasn’t transformation — it was elevation. The bride wore a soft, dewy glam look that highlighted her natural glow — think radiant skin, softly flushed cheeks, feathered brows, and a hint of shimmer on the lids. Her lips? Just a touch of rosy tint, like she’s been smiling all day (because she has).

For the groom, we kept it effortlessly fresh — a light touch to even out skin tone, reduce shine, and bring out his natural charm. The result? A clean, confident look that photographs like a dream and feels like him.

Together, they looked like the best version of themselves — in love, glowing, and completely them.
